article.headline: Oral Roberts 87, Valparaiso 78
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Caleb Green scored 27 points and grabbed 15 rebounds to lead Oral Roberts to a 87-78 win over Valparaiso Saturday night. Green, who entered the game averaging 21 points and 8.6 rebounds per game, picked up his 13th double-double of the season. It was the tenth consecutive loss for Valparaiso (16-11, 8-8 Mid-Continent Conference) at Oral Roberts since 1997. Oral Roberts (18-11, 13-3) trailed for much of the first half before taking a 38-35 lead at halftime. Jonathan Bluitt opened the second half with a 3-pointer to spark a second-half surge by the Golden Eagles. A put-back dunk by Yemi Ogunoye with 11:45 remaining stretched ORU's lead to 56-47. After Green picked up his fourth foul with 8:46 left, Valparaiso rallied but couldn't get closer than six points. Dan Oppland led Valparaiso with 25 points and 12 rebounds.
